                {
                    "id": "slide_3_shape_1",
                    "type": "text_box",
                    "text": "Markov Decision Process (MDP) is a mathematical formulation of decision making. An agent is the decision maker. In the reinforcement learning framework, he is the learner or the decision maker. \n\nWe need to give this agent information so that it is able to learn to decide. As such, an MDP is a tuple: ⟨𝑆,𝐴,𝑃,𝛾,𝑅⟩ that is (State, Action, Probability Transitions, discount factor, Reward).\n\nIt is basically all you need to know about the problem to be able to make a good decision to optimally perform a task.",
                    "position": {
                        "x": 144.0,
                        "y": 161.07,
                        "width": 1075.2,
                        "height": 454.93
                    },
                    "style": {
                        "font_size": 25.0,
                        "bold": false,
                        "italic": false,
                        "color": null,
                        "background_color": null
                    },
